#######################################
#  Solution

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_SOLUTION
The correct answer is ${BBOLD}B${EBOLD}.
If \( f \) is differentiable at \( a \), 
it must be continuous at \( a \).
Therefore, by the definition of continuity 
\( \displaystyle \lim_{x \to a} f(x) = f(a) \).
END_SOLUTION
